<h1>Mally&rsquo;s Deontic Logic</h1><div id="pubinfo"><em>First published Fri Apr 5, 2002; substantive revision Fri Jan 30, 2026</em></div>

<div id="preamble">

<p>
In 1926, Mally presented the first formal system of deontic logic. His
system had several consequences which Mally regarded as surprising but
defensible. It also had a consequence (&ldquo;A is obligatory if and
only if A is the case&rdquo;) which Menger (1939) and almost all later
deontic logicians have regarded as unacceptable. We will not only
describe Mally&rsquo;s system but also discuss how it may be
repaired.</p>
</div> 

